OL,3,CPreventing a 'lost generation' of
OL,4,Cyoung people and is it time to revisit
OL,5,CBrexit?
OL,7,FTom Sheldrick's panel consider how
OL,8,Fmore jobs and training can be
OL,9,Fprovided, the toll of unemployment on
OL,10,Fyoung people's mental health - and why
OL,11,Fsociety urgently needs to help them
OL,12,Finto the workplace:
OL,14,FThe former Darlington Labour MP and
OL,15,Fformer Health Secretary Alan Milburn
OL,16,Fhas described the cohort of 16-24 year
OL,17,Folds currently not in education,
OL,18,Ftraining or employment as 'a
OL,19,Fgeneration in genuine distress.'
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G1/4
