OL,3,CPreventing a 'lost generation' of
OL,4,Cyoung people and is it time to revisit
OL,5,CBrexit?
OL,7,FHis first report on Young People and
OL,8,FWork has put the plight of more than a
OL,9,Fmillion young adults at the heart of
OL,10,Fthe political debate.
OL,12,FRecommendations for action will follow
OL,13,Fin the Autumn, but his assessment is
OL,14,Fclear, the problem of being Not in
OL,15,FEducation, Employment of Training
OL,16,F(NEET) is grounded in social
OL,17,Fdisadvantage.
OL,19,FIn the North East, more than a fifth
OL,20,Fof 16 to 24 year olds are not learning
OL,21,For earning.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
